HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 740
By Carringer
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Dogwood Arts upon the
occasion of its seventieth anniversary.
WHEREAS, it is the privilege of the members of this General Assembly to recognize
those venerable cultural institutions that exist to foster and perpetuate the arts and enrich the
places they call home; and
WHEREAS, one such organization is Dogwood Arts, which celebrated its seventieth
anniversary in 2025, marking seven decades of arts advocacy, environmental stewardship, and
economic impact in East Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, the seeds for Dogwood Arts were planted in 1955, when members of the
Knoxville Garden Club, led by Betsey Creekmore, Martha Ashe, and Betsy Goodson, along with
a group of concerned citizens with a vision began a civic beautification project—the Dogwood
Trails; and
WHEREAS, the organization's premier event, the Dogwood Arts Festival, was first held
in 1961, with Bob Hope attending in 1970; the festival marked half a century of celebrating the
arts in 2010; and
WHEREAS, the House and Garden Show was established in 1978, and the following
year saw the establishment of A Very Special Arts Festival; the organization's other banner
events include Chalk Walk, Rhythm N' Blooms, and Bazillion Blooms, which, since 2009, has
helped plant more than 18,500 dogwood trees; and
WHEREAS, in honor of its seventieth anniversary, Dogwood Arts is highlighting its
annual Bazillion Blooms campaign, selling disease-resistant, April-blooming dogwood trees to
help preserve the region's natural beauty and "Keep Knoxville Blooming" for generations to
come; and
HJR0740
009812
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Dogwood Arts has enriched the arts and culture of Knoxville and beautified
the city for seven decades, and it is fitting that the organization be honored; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Dogwood Arts upon the occasion of its seventieth
anniversary, extending our sincere gratitude for the good work of this organization and our best
wishes for its continued success in the future.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
